summary: This code reads input from stdin, concatenates it into a single string, splits the string into words, converts them to a set (removing duplicates), and finally joins the words back together with spaces before printing.

details.comment: This code reads input from stdin, concatenates it into a single string, splits the string into words, converts them to a set (removing duplicates), and finally joins the words back together with spaces before printing.
details.content:
import sys
v=""
for x in sys.stdin:
    v+=x
v = v.split()
v = set(v)
v = " ".join(v)
print(v)
